"```sql\nSELECT MAX(ta.chanceCreationPassing) AS highest_chance_creation_passing_score, ta.chanceCreationPassingClass\nFROM Team t\nJOIN Team_Attributes ta ON t.team_api_id = ta.team_api_id\nWHERE t.team_long_name = 'Ajax'\nGROUP BY ta.chanceCreationPassingClass\nORDER BY highest_chance_creation_passing_score DESC\nLIMIT 1;\n```\n\nThis SQL query selects the highest chance creation passing score for the team Ajax and its classification. It joins the `Team` and `Team_Attributes` tables using the `team_api_id` and filters for the team with the long name 'Ajax'. It groups the results by the `chanceCreationPassingClass` and orders them to get the highest score."